{
  "texts": [
    "For Mamba layers, we follow [4] to define the attention pattern, while for Transformer layers, we use the attention weights.",
    "Definition of attention score.",
    "For self-attention (Equation (2)), the attention score M j,i ∈ R from x j to x i is:y i = Softmax( Q i K T ≤i √ D) • V ≤i = i j=1 M i,j V j (7)For the SSM block, we rewrite Equation (1) to express its attention pattern as the weighted sum from inputs [x 1,..., x i] to the output y i:y i = i j=1 C T i ( i k=j+1 A k)B j x j = i j=1 M ′ i,j x j(8)Here, |M ′ i,j | ∈ R + serves as the \"attention score\" [4, 119] from x j to x i within the SSM block.",
    "Although both the self-attention and Mamba mechanisms employ a multi-head design [23,83] along the hidden dimension, we omit this detail in the equations for simplicity.",
    "Diverse and specialized attention patterns in Mamba layers."
  ]
}